🧠 IRSA FULL WORKFLOW (EKS + S3) – Hinglish Notes
🎯 Use Case
Pod A → S3 access ✅
Pod B → S3 access ✅
Pod C → No access ❌
🔥 Step 1: OIDC Provider enable

👉 Amazon EKS ko IAM se connect karte hain

eksctl utils associate-iam-oidc-provider \
  --cluster my-cluster \
  --approve

👉 Ye trust establish karta hai between EKS & AWS IAM

🔥 Step 2: IAM Policy (S3 access)

👉 Amazon S3 ke liye permissions

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Action": ["s3:GetObject", "s3:PutObject"],
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::my-bucket/*"
    }
  ]
}
🔥 Step 3: IAM Role (IRSA Role)

👉 Is role ko upar wali policy attach karte hain

🔑 Trust Policy (important)
OIDC provider use hota hai
Specific service account restrict hota hai

👉 Key line:

system:serviceaccount:<namespace>:s3-access-sa
🔥 Step 4: Kubernetes Service Account
apiVersion: v1
kind: ServiceAccount
metadata:
  name: s3-access-sa
  namespace: default
  annotations:
    eks.amazonaws.com/role-arn: arn:aws:iam::<ACCOUNT_ID>:role/s3-access-role

👉 Ye bridge hai pod ↔ IAM role

🔥 Step 5: Pod Configuration
✅ Pod A & B (S3 access)
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: pod-a
spec:
  serviceAccountName: s3-access-sa
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: amazonlinux

👉 Pod B same config use karega

❌ Pod C (No access)
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: pod-c
spec:
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: amazonlinux

👉 Default service account → no IAM role → no S3 access
